# If you prefer the allow list template instead of the deny list, see community template:
# https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/main/community/Golang/Go.AllowList.gitignore
#
# Binaries for programs and plugins
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib

# Test binary, built with `go test -c`
*.test

# Code coverage profiles and other test artifacts
*.out
coverage.*
*.coverprofile
profile.cov

# Dependency directories (remove the comment below to include it)
# vendor/

# Vendored dependencies for the offline thin Compose proof's Docker build
# (issue #79 Task 0.3, `mise run thinproof-build`) -- a build-time artifact
# regenerated by `go mod vendor`, never committed.
vendor/

# Go workspace file
go.work
go.work.sum

# env file
.env

# Editor/IDE
# .idea/
# .vscode/

# macOS Finder metadata
.DS_Store

# JS package build outputs (js/semantics)
js/semantics/node_modules/
js/semantics/dist/
js/semantics/dist-test/
js/semantics/bin/
js/semantics/vendor/wasm_exec.js
*.wasm

# Generated output from the thin offline Compose proof (issue #79 Task 0.3)
deploy/compose/thinproof/output/*
!deploy/compose/thinproof/output/.gitkeep

tmp
